## Educational License Terms

This project is specifically designed as an educational resource with the following additional terms:

### Learning and Educational Use
- This code is primarily human-written for educational purposes
- AI assistance was used for code review, optimization, and documentation
- Students and learners are encouraged to study, modify, and learn from this code
- Educational institutions may use this project for teaching purposes

### Attribution Requirements
- Maintain original author attribution when using or modifying this code
- Clearly indicate any modifications made to the original source
- If using this project as a learning reference, acknowledge the source

### Commercial Use Guidelines
- Commercial use is permitted under MIT License terms
- Consider contributing improvements back to the educational community
- Respect the educational nature of the extensively commented code

### Responsible Use
- Users must comply with platform terms of service when downloading media
- Respect copyright laws and content creators' rights
- Use only for personal or educational purposes unless properly licensed
- The author is not responsible for misuse of the software

### Developer Learning Focus
This project prioritizes:
- Code readability and educational value over performance optimization
- Extensive commenting for learning purposes
- Clear architectural patterns for educational demonstration
- Best practices in modern web development
